Poor man's (cheapskate) substitute:

http://www.harborfreight.com/cpi/ctaf/displayitem.taf?Itemnumber=31555

Have many of these or similar. Great to have in tool kit in each old car.

For a 1/8" bit I would buy a set of inexpensive "jeweler's" screwdrivers -
this is what I use.

http://www.harborfreight.com/cpi/ctaf/displayitem.taf?Itemnumber=6904
